<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–1046: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-10-10">October 10,
                                1946</date>.<lb/>[Received October 10—2:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1628. Embassy spokesman made following announcement at 6:30 p.m., October
                            9:</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“General Marshall flew to Shanghai this morning to see General Chou
                                En Lai and conferred with him there. General Marshall returned to
                                Nanking at 6 p.m.”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>